UPDATE public.questions SET
  stimulus_text = 'In the early 1990s, as a response to the popularity of compact discs, some record labels began reissuing their albums on vinyl. This was seen as a niche market catering to audiophiles who preferred the warmth and sound of analog recordings. However, by the late 2000s, vinyl records had gained a broader appeal. Younger generations were drawn to the tactile experience of vinyl and the accompanying album art. The resurgence of vinyl records is a testament to the enduring appeal of analog sound and the artistic value of music beyond its digital format.',
